        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> Howdy.</P><P>The July 24 news on eq.castersrealm.com stated the following:</P><P>PATCH MESSAGE<BR>Today's patch message is out and contains a lot of changes. Here's a summary:</P><P>    * The new interface is now available to players.<BR>    * The Bazaar is now available to players.<BR>    * A new zone: Jaggedpine Forest is now available to players.<BR>    * Moving NPCs will no longer receive a reduction in DoT damage.<BR>    * Fear & Charm will no longer work against any player on any server when cast by another player.<BR>    * The bug to use charmed pets to have NPC's assist with kills has been fixed.<BR>    * Vah Shir Models for the Old World have been added that are less memory intensive.<BR>    * The Vex Thal key quest has been modified.<BR>    * Pets will now resist spells differently.</P><P>Note item 4 in the list... is that suggesting that npcs now take full dot damage (instead of 66%) while they're chasing you?  If so, this takes us way back to the good old days, before the first big nerf.</P><P>Can anyone confirm this behavior?</P><P>Kadava - Zebuxoruk</P><P> </font></td>

