        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Nothing worng with aggro kiting, but the fact is you generally regen more mana than you spend on the fear by medding while the mob is feared, than have it chase you the whole time.  At least its that way for me.  Root cooking imo is situational now.  I used to do it because it was too much of a hassle to KS pet all the time.  Now you want pet to do as much damage as possible, so its really not the most effecient way to xp anymore.  If a mob can be feared, and it has a reasonable resist, and last rate, then im going to fear kite.</P><P>BTW if you have problems with the mob getting too far away, use reg fear instead of invoke.  Also learn how to med hop.  Sit for the tick .. run 5 secs ... sit .. etc.</P><P><p><font face="Arial" color="#ff9900" font size="2"><palign="center"><strong>Retrievil Hesevil<br><BR>'If you have a problem, if no one else can help, and if you can<BR>find him, maybe you can hire ... The Evil One.'<br><BR>-Tallon Zek -</p><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
